            <h2 id="what-heading" class="reveal-up font-heading font-bold text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-brand-900 tracking-tight mb-5">What is a Double Hung <span class="text-brand-500">Window?</span></h2>
            <p class="reveal-up text-lg text-slate-500 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              A double-hung window features <strong class="text-slate-700">two operable sashes</strong> that slide vertically within the frame. Unlike single-hung windows where only the bottom moves, both the upper and lower sashes can be raised or lowered independently — giving you more control over airflow and easier maintenance.
            </p>
            <p class="reveal-up text-lg text-slate-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">
              Modern double-hung windows use a spring-loaded balance system that holds each sash in any position without slamming shut. Most models also feature <strong class="text-slate-700">tilt-in sashes</strong> — each panel pivots inward on release latches, allowing you to clean the exterior glass from inside your home.
            </p>

